    <p>MELBOURNE • Aus­tralian Bob Brett, who coached for­mer ten­nis world No. 1 Boris Becker in his stand­out 1989 sea­son dur­ing which he won Wim­ble­don and the US Open, yes­ter­day died of can­cer at the age of 67.</p>
    <p>In a 46-year ca­reer, Brett also worked with Jo­han Kriek, Go­ran Ivani­se­vic, Mats Wi­lan­der and Marin Cilic, as well as many na­tional ten­nis as­so­ci­a­tions.</p>


